The paper deals with encoding local features for writer identification and retrieval using CNN activations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses techniques such as generalized max pooling and Exemplar SVMs, which are commonly used in machine learning and information retrieval, indicating that the paper could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on publicly available datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
